    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER - REASSEMBLE - MAINSHAFT AND COUNTERSHAFTS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="8">
        <title>MAINSHAFT AND COUNTERSHAFTS</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the 4th-5th shift collar on the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302366">Figure 66</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302366" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302366" filename="../figg13/G1302366.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 66. Mainshaft and Countershaft Reassembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install 4th and 3rd speed gears into place (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302367">Figure 67</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302367" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302367" filename="../figg13/G1302367.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 67. Install 4th &#38; 3rd Speed Gears</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the 2nd-3rd shift collar (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302368">Figure 68</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302368" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302368" filename="../figg13/G1302368.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 68. Install 2nd - 3rd Shift Collar</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the mainshaft assembly spacer (ZTSE4287) onto the shift collar (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302369">Figure 69</hotlnk>). Center the bolt with the fork bracket slot. This tool
                holds the collar at the proper height for receiving the countershafts.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302369" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302369" filename="../figg13/G1302369.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 69. Install Mainshaft Assembly Spacer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install 2nd and 1st speed gears (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302370">Figure 70</hotlnk>). Visually center the gears on the shaft.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302370" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302370" filename="../figg13/G1302370.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 70. Install 2nd and 1st Speed Gears</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install 1st-reverse shift collar (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302371">Figure 71</hotlnk>). Secure it with the snap ring.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302371" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302371" filename="../figg13/G1302371.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 71. Install 1st - Reverse Shift Collar</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the countershafts together (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302372">Figure 72</hotlnk>). The blind splines are timing marks. Align them across
                from one another.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302372" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302372" filename="../figg13/G1302372.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 72. Slide Countershafts Together</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach the gear shaft lifting fixture (ZTSE4288) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302373">Figure 73</hotlnk>). Remove the mainshaft assembly spacer.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302373" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302373" filename="../figg13/G1302373.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 73. Attach Lifting Fixture</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
